## Public Member Functions

### at() {#a3fd7e15638d42fca988fddf2481a4dd2}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename ValueType, typename Extractor = VarStreamArrayExtractor&lt;ValueType&gt;&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>Iterator llvm::VarStreamArray&lt; ValueType, Extractor &gt;::at (uint32&#95;t Offset) const</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
given an offset into the array&#39;s underlying stream, return an iterator to the record at that offset.

This is considered unsafe since the behavior is undefined if <code>Offset</code> does not refer to the beginning of a valid record.
